{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.21",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 21 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:1",
      "text": "The king's heart is a stream of water in the hand of the Lord; he turns it wherever he will.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:2",
      "text": "Every way of a man is right in his own eyes, but the Lord weighs the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:3",
      "text": "To do righteousness and justice is more acceptable to the Lord than sacrifice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:4",
      "text": "Haughty eyes and a proud heart, the lamp of the wicked, are sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:5",
      "text": "The plans of the diligent lead surely to abundance, but every one who is hasty comes only to want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:6",
      "text": "The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a fleeting vapor and a snare of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:7",
      "text": "The violence of the wicked will sweep them away, because they refuse to do what is just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:8",
      "text": "The way of the guilty is crooked, but the conduct of the pure is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:9",
      "text": "It is better to live in a corner of the housetop than in a house shared with a contentious woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:10",
      "text": "The soul of the wicked desires evil; his neighbor finds no mercy in his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:11",
      "text": "When a scoffer is punished, the simple becomes wise; when a wise man is instructed, he gains knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:12",
      "text": "The righteous observes the house of the wicked; the wicked are cast down to ruin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:13",
      "text": "He who closes his ear to the cry of the poor will himself cry out and not be heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:14",
      "text": "A gift in secret averts anger; and a bribe in the bosom, strong wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:15",
      "text": "When justice is done, it is a joy to the righteous, but dismay to evildoers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:16",
      "text": "A man who wanders from the way of understanding will rest in the assembly of the dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:17",
      "text": "He who loves pleasure will be a poor man; he who loves wine and oil will not be rich.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:18",
      "text": "The wicked is a ransom for the righteous, and the faithless for the upright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:19",
      "text": "It is better to live in a desert land than with a contentious and fretful woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:20",
      "text": "Precious treasure remains in a wise man's dwelling, but a foolish man devours it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:21",
      "text": "He who pursues righteousness and kindness will find life and honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:22",
      "text": "A wise man scales the city of the mighty and brings down the stronghold in which they trust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:23",
      "text": "He who keeps his mouth and his tongue keeps himself out of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:24",
      "text": "“Scoffer” is the name of the proud, haughty man who acts with arrogant pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:25",
      "text": "The desire of the sluggard kills him for his hands refuse to labor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:26",
      "text": "All day long the wicked covets, but the righteous gives and does not hold back.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:27",
      "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination; how much more when he brings it with evil intent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:28",
      "text": "A false witness will perish, but the word of a man who hears will endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:29",
      "text": "A wicked man puts on a bold face, but an upright man considers his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:30",
      "text": "No wisdom, no understanding, no counsel, can avail against the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.21.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:31",
      "text": "The horse is made ready for the day of battle, but the victory belongs to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
